==Notable figures== *[[Shimon Avidan]] – Palestinian Jew and future [[Israel]]i military officer. *[[Alfred Brauner]] – French Austrian communist, scholar and author *[[Robert Domany]] – [[Croatia]]n [[Yugoslav Partisans|Partisan]] and a [[People's Hero of Yugoslavia]] *[[Gershon Dua-Bogen]] – Polish communist *[[Fernando Gerassi]] – Turkish artist *[[Kurt Julius Goldstein]] – [[International Brigade]]r, Holocaust survivor, and author *[[David Guest (communist)|David Guest]] – Communist British mathematician and philosopher. *{{Interlanguage link multi|Alfred Kantorowicz|de}} – banned German writer (also known as ''Helmuth Campe'') *[[Lou Kenton]] – British potter *{{Interlanguage link multi|Artur Kerschner|sr|3=Артур Кершнер}} – Croatian student *[[Bert "Yank" Levy]] – a Canadian who famously used his experience to teach the [[British Home Guard]] and wrote a text on [[guerrilla warfare]]<ref name="ANB">{{cite web |first1=Allan E. |last1=Levine |url=http://www.anb.org/articles/20/20-01892.html |publisher=[[Oxford University Press]] |work=[[American National Biography]] on line |accessdate=April 16, 2014 |title=Bert "Yank" Levy}}</ref><ref>{{cite book |url=http://www.solargeneral.com/library/guerrilla-warfare-by-yank-bert-levy.pdf |title=Guerilla Warfare |first1=Bert "Yank" |last1=Levy |authorlink1="Yank" Levy |first2=Tom (Foreword) |last2=Wintringham |authorlink2=Tom Wintringham |origyear=1942|year=1964 |publisher=Paladin Press |format=[[PDF]] |accessdate=April 15, 2014}}</ref> His service in the Civil War was memorialized in a [[comic book]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://comicbookplus.com/?dlid=27391 |title=Jewish War Heroes |publisher=[[Canadian Jewish Congress]] |type=Comic book |number=1 |date=February 1944 |accessdate=April 16, 2014}}</ref> *[[Vladimir Majder]] – [[Croatia]]n [[Yugoslav Partisans|Partisan]] and communist *[[George Nathan]] – Chief of Staff of the [[XV International Brigade]] *[[Abe Osheroff]] – American communist *[[Valter Roman]] – Romanian politician *[[Carlo Rosselli]] – headed the [[Matteotti Battalion]] *[[Alfred Sherman]] – British journalist and adviser to [[Margaret Thatcher]] *[[Jack Shulman]] – American communist *[[Manfred Stern]] alias General Emilio Kléber *[[Drago Štajnberger]] – [[Croatia]]n [[Yugoslav Partisans|Partisan]] and a [[People's Hero of Yugoslavia]] *Saul Wellman – political commissar of the [[Lincoln Battalion]] and the [[Washington Battalion]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.metrotimes.com/editorial/story.asp?id=5761|title=Fare thee Wellman|work=Detroit Metro Times}}</ref> *[[Milton Wolff]] – commander of the [[Lincoln Battalion]] *[[Máté Zalka]] – Hungarian communist
